"{\n  \"correct\": \"no\",\n  \"explanation\": \"The code is trying to customize the seaborn styles by passing a dictionary of parameters to the set_context() function. However, according to the seaborn documentation, the dictionary of parameters should be passed to the rc argument of axes_style() or set_style() functions, or the set_theme() function. The set_context() function is used to set the plotting context, not to override style parameters.\",\n  \"patch\": \"9c9\\n---\\n>sns.set_theme(rc=viz_dict)\\n\"\n}"